result.formatted_address: 4號 Tai Pa St, Tsuen Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Xin Dau Ji

reviews.text: Good suckling pig and bbq goose. If u happened to be in the neighborhood and wanted good suckling pig, it's worth the try.
Dim sum good, service good. Dont miss trying out the barbecued goose. The tables were  a bit too closely placed.
Nice Chinese food, Dum sum.

Finally have the chance to try this popular restaurant at their Tsuen Wan outlet but was disappointed. Ordered the $368 set dinner with suckling pig, fried prawn and seafood mixed vegetable pot. The suckling pig seemed was roasted a while and lost the crispiness, the prawns had mo taste while the veggie was fresh but over-cooked. Overall not as good as it should have been given the high price they charge.
Two other things annoyed me. The chopsticks were oily. Though they gave customers a bowl to wash the eating utensils (a tradition for traditional Chinese tea house/restaurant or now at grassroot lower class restaurants), as a mid to high class restaurant, they should maintain a high hygenic standard. Another thing is they automatically served a tiny dish of fried peanuts which was tasteless (not even seasoned with anything like salt) which costed $10 + 10%. Again this is the practice in the old days when tips were not commonly given and the money was supposed to be for the waiters and other employees like tips. But now, with 10% service charge added to the bill automatically and some customer would also give small extra tips, I doubt the money will benefit the employees. 
Lastly, the facts that tables were still available at the peak hour 7:30 pm on a Sunday evening and the restaurant was more than half empty before 9 pm did reflect something wrong with the restaurant.
good taste, but a bit crowded

reviews.text: 點心雖不花巧，但食物質素優
無論食物及點心均有水準， 有食過返尋味的感覺。
食物貴價唔飽，越來越唔好食，但唔緊要，最緊要的是最近服務員態度越來越差，特別係門口支客，咁多年熟客也得罪，以後絕對不會再去
港式粵菜酒摟，平日晚市現金消費有优惠或以信用卡結賬，可亨兩小時商塲免費泊車，交通方便。
